    <title>the-cost-of-writing-exploited-html</title>
    <link href="https://bloodyaugust.github.io/frontend-feed/2019/06/28/the-cost-of-writing-exploited-html/"/>
    <id>https://bloodyaugust.github.io/frontend-feed/2019/06/28/the-cost-of-writing-exploited-html/</id>
    <published>2019-06-28T21:15:25.000Z</published>
    <updated>2019-06-28T21:25:22.444Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul><li><p><a href="https://v8.dev/blog/cost-of-javascript-2019" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Cost of JavaScript in 2019</a> - An analysis of what your JS is doing that takes up time, and how to optimize it. - <a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="http://john.ankarstrom.se/html/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Writing HTML in HTML</a> - A kind-of-tongue-in-cheek article discussing the benefits of using pure HTML over a static site generator. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2cyib2MgvdM" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Analysis of an Exploited NPM Package</a> - A presentation that dives into the <code>event-stream</code> vulnerability from last year, and how we can avoid this problem going forward. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li></ul>]]></content>
    
