    <title>state-of-the-cli-web-components</title>
    <link href="https://bloodyaugust.github.io/frontend-feed/2019/06/21/state-of-the-cli-web-components/"/>
    <id>https://bloodyaugust.github.io/frontend-feed/2019/06/21/state-of-the-cli-web-components/</id>
    <published>2019-06-21T21:35:39.000Z</published>
    <updated>2019-06-21T21:48:38.579Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul><li><p><a href="https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/blob/function-apis/active-rfcs/0000-function-api.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vue Gets Functional Components</a> - Akin to how React components work, this proposal is still just that, but pretty interesting. - <a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://blog.bitsrc.io/debugging-javascript-like-a-pro-a2e0f6c53c2e" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Debugging JS Like A Pro</a> - A great walkthru on how to use Chrome tools when debugging your frontend. - <a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.robinwieruch.de/web-components-tutorial/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Components For Beginners</a> - Another great tutorial on what WC are, how they are useful, and how to write/implement them. - <a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://gist.github.com/aeschright/8ed09cbc2a4aee00fcb4ad35086d76a6" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shit Is Going Down At NPM</a> - NPM has fired numerous employees for “discussing workplace conditions and other labor organizing activities”. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://2019.stateofcss.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">State of CSS</a> - The who, what, how, where, why of using CSS in the modern web, there are some <em>very</em> interesting statistics here. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li></ul>]]></content>
    
