    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul><li><p><a href="https://twitter.com/nicolaschevobbe/status/1135798960361263104" target="_blank" rel="noopener">New Firefox No CSS Effect Tool</a> - A tweet referencing a new feature in FF that helps you understand why a CSS attribute isn’t working. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.matuzo.at/blog/building-the-most-inaccessible-site-possible-with-a-perfect-lighthouse-score/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Inaccessible But Perfect: A Lighthouse Tale</a> - A fun exercise that shows how automated tests are no replacement for good old design and testing. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://snyk.io/blog/npm-passes-the-1-millionth-package-milestone-what-can-we-learn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NPM Hits 1 Million Packages</a> - A fun look at how <code>npm</code> has grown over time, and some of the more popular packages. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://github.com/tc39/proposal-optional-chaining" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Optional Chaining Is Coming To JS</a> - Those of you with one foot in the world of Ruby are really going to appreciate this one. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li></ul>]]></content>
    
