    <published>2019-05-24T22:08:47.000Z</published>
    <updated>2019-05-24T22:20:37.712Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul><li><p><a href="https://roughjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RoughJS</a> - Programmatically render hand-drawn shapes with this super cool library. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://github.blog/2019-05-23-announcing-github-sponsors-a-new-way-to-contribute-to-open-source/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Github Sponsors</a> - Like everyone else, Github now has a native “Patreon”. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://medium.com/goodboy-digital/pixijs-v5-lands-5e112d84e510" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PixiJS 5 Release</a> - The amazing and all-encompassing PixiJS releases a huge new version, ditching <code>Context2D</code> and gaining a lot of cool stuff. - <a href="gamedevjsweekly.com">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://jrsinclair.com/articles/2019/functional-js-do-more-with-reduce/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Using <code>[].reduce</code></a> - Great tutorial on how <code>reduce</code> serves as the basis for all things functional programming. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://blog.logrocket.com/truly-reactive-programming-with-svelte-3-0-321b49b75969" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Svelte</a> - A great article explaining <em>what</em> Svelte is and <em>why</em> you should use it (spoilers: compiler, reactivity). - <a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li></ul>]]></content>
    
