    <id>https://bloodyaugust.github.io/frontend-feed/2019/05/10/evergreen-conspiracy/</id>
    <published>2019-05-10T21:39:56.000Z</published>
    <updated>2019-05-10T21:49:43.263Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul><li><p><a href="https://webmasters.googleblog.com/2019/05/the-new-evergreen-googlebot.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Googlebot Goes Evergreen</a> - Googlebot is now an (mostly) evergreen project, bringing us a step closer to a fully modern web. - <a href="https://webmasters.googleblog.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="http://blog.chriszacharias.com/a-conspiracy-to-kill-ie6" target="_blank" rel="noopener">A Conspiracy To Kill IE6</a> - An interesting (and perhaps cautionary) tale about how a major player knocked another out of the ring. - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://victorzhou.com/blog/build-an-io-game-part-1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How To Build An IO Game</a> - Less gamedev focused, more about how to build massively scaling realtime node services. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.twilio.com/blog/how-to-build-a-cli-with-node-js" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How To Build A CLI In Node</a> - There are so many CLI building tools available in node, learn what they are and how to use them. - <a href="https://nodeweekly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://webkit.org/blog/8840/dark-mode-support-in-webkit/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dark Mode Support In Webkit</a> - Finally, the light has lost. Viva la Dark Mode! - <a href="https://frontendfoc.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From</a></p></li></ul>]]></content>
    
